  "course_description": "Students will learn the craft of research in economics. Coursework will consist of synthesis of literature; collection, collation, cleaning of data; data analysis, contributing to manuscript preparation, and/or other work related to the sustaining of an academic research project.",
  "course_notes": "Federal Reserve Challenge In this course, we will examine the tools of monetary policy used to achieve the Federal Reserve's dual mandate of maximum employment and price stability. Drawing on macroeconomic theory, data analysis, and current research, we will assess prevailing economic conditions and evaluate policy alternatives. The class will develop a formal monetary policy recommendation for the U.S. central bank, emulating the deliberative process of the Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC). Students will then present the class's recommendation in the annual Fed Challenge Competition, More details can be found here- https://www.federalreserve.gov/conferences/fedchallenge.htm. )",
